   COLOMBIA-U.S. (United Nations) _ In an interview, President
Andres Pastrana of Colombia insists that despite his government's
request for a huge new infusion of aid from abroad, the United
States will not be drawn more deeply into its 40-year fight against
leftist guerrillas. By Tim Golden.
</P>
