debilitating, that it can't be overridden by a product at the
drugstore. Advertising in general is pretty much the art of coaxing
us to spend money we don't have for products we don't need because
they can't really deliver on the promises the advertisements hint
at. If something is both new and improved, wouldn't that only make
it better than nothing? But advertising medical products requires a
level of responsibility that advertisers don't normally display.
(Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
