<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0921 _ Although they have the aerodynamic
qualities of cinder blocks, the Ford F-150s that emerge from the
Special Vehicle Team, or SVT, shop become ferocious,
pavement-scorching Lightnings ready for the drag strip. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 4-column color photo of
Ford F-150 Lightning and a 18-pica color photo of the truck's
interior.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Ford G-150 Lightning
truck.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING _ Goodyear's marketing folks aren't missing an
opportunity to jump on the NASCAR bandwagon. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color photograph of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   ECLIPSE-REVIEW _ A review of the 2000 Mitsubishi Eclipse coupe
(DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL FINANCE
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ I get lots of mail from readers who want to know how
to make more money from their investments. I get even more mail
from people who want to make more and avoid paying taxes on their
successes. People feel that they are the ones taking the risks, so
they shouldn't have to share the rewards with the Internal Revenue
Service. Many are agitated by the suspicion that somebody else is
getting better tax breaks than they are. Then there's just plain
greed. But too many people get carried away about tax avoidance.
(Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   JUVENILE-DIABETES _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Ben Newell was only 4 when he
went on his first Walk to Cure Diabetes two years ago. As he and
his parents reached their car afterward, Ben had a question. ``Is
my diabetes cured now?'' he said. The disease shared by 16 million
Americans remains incurable, but the prospects are looking more
hopeful. Last spring saw a vaccine that prevented the development
of Type I, juvenile diabetes, in mice. Summer brought news of
possible genetic manipulation that would enable people to grow the
insulin-producing cells that are missing in juvenile diabetics.
Research continues on transplanting pancreatic islet cells for the
same purpose. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   CMA-PREVIEW _ Our preview of the Country Music Association
Awards show (the most important one in country music), is a guide
to what to look for in the show, including: 1) family feud over
Conway Twitty's posthumous induction into the Hall of Fame, 2)
Porter Wagoner's response to Dolly Parton getting into hall of fame
before he does, 3) controversy over George Jones' refusing to sing
song if it must be cut and others (like Lee Ann Rimes) refusing to
perform because of this. Includes comments from host Vince Gill.
(MLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   TV-WESTWING _ Review of ``West Wing,'' possibly the most buzzed
about show of the new season, written by Aaron Sorkin (''The
American President,'' ``Sports Night''), starring Rob Lowe and
Martin Sheen (the rest of the cast are very talented, but not
famous names). (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   WOLF-WESTWING _ Wolf Blitzer, the longtime CNN Washington
correspondent who is now anchor of the network's new one-hour
weekday news, watches ``West Wing'' and gives us his take on the
show and its depiction of the White House, the White House press
corps and Washington. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TULIP-BULBS _ Fall begins today, and spring bulbs are popping up
daily in garden centers, mail-order catalogs and Web sites. More
than a half-million will be sold in the United States, and this
fall shoppers are expected to flock to tulips in particular.
Fueling their interest are a half-dozen new books and even a film
planned for release in spring by movie mogul Steven Spielberg about
the simple bulb's rich history. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) with COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Thursday, Sept. 23.
</P>
