   TIMOR-INDONESIA (Jakarta) _ Disliked at home, discredited
abroad, and discounted by virtually everyone, Indonesia's
president, B.J. Habibie, trudged into the parliament on Tuesday to
explain his decision to allow foreign troops into East Timor. By
Mark Landler.
