<P>
   TAIWAN-QUAKE _ TAICHUNG, Taiwan _ Stunned Taiwanese were digging
out Tuesday from a killer earthquake that wrenched villages and
towns apart, at least 1,455 dead and 1,000 trapped in buildings.
Most of the escalating count of dead, missing and maimed
concentrated in central Taiwan, near the epicenter of the monster
quake that registered 7.6 on the Richter scale. The U.S. Geological
Survey's National Earthquake Information Center put the quake's
epicenter was centered 90 miles south of Taipei. Hardest hit were
the counties of Taichung and Nantou, where more than 1,000 were
reported dead and another 1,000 still trapped in the rubble of
buildings. (Kunstel/Albright, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
