<HEADLINE>
EIGHT WAYS TO TELL AUTUMN IS HERE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MARY E. SCHULTE  
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Today's the first day of fall, and you know it's so because:
</P>
<P>
   1. The cat snuggles under the covers instead of sleeping at the
end of the bed.
</P>
<P>
   2. The usually rambunctious dogs have to be shoved out the door
in the morning.
</P>
<P>
   3. We see our breath as we leave for school.
</P>
<P>
   4. Our jackets, bought sizes too big to last several winters,
need to be replaced now.
</P>
<P>
   5. A bowl of steaming oatmeal tastes great for breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   6. The question of the morning is ``Where are the hats and
gloves?''
</P>
<P>
   7. The heater in the van finally gets warm as we pull into the
school driveway.
</P>
<P>
   8. The golden glow of the morning sun reminds you of the
beautiful fall colors on the way.
</P>
</TEXT>
