summer is history as of Wednesday. Looking back, the Summer of '99
wasn't a record-breaker, not by a long shot. But the relentless
combination of high temperatures, if not record readings, and high
humidity took its toll: nearly 30 area residents succumbed to it.
We try to assess the costs in human and financial terms. Shawna
Hamel. 18-22. Photos
