rivers is in the midst of an oldtimer-newcomer feud. Weirich
Brothers Co., which has mined sand and gravel from the riverbeds
for years, wants an air pollution permit to produce asphalt. The
newly arrived environmental refugees from cities like Houston and
Dallas are having apoplexy. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
