   RELIGION-JONES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ When Dr. Larry Dossey began practicing as an internist
in Dallas several years ago, he was an agnostic who never
considered praying for his patients. ``I was skeptical of all this
religious stuff,'' Dossey said. Not anymore. Dossey, a highly
respected physician who was chief of staff of Medical City Dallas
in the 1980s, now is the nation's most passionate advocate of
combining faith and the practice of medicine. By JIM JONES. Story
has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
