   BLACKS _CREDIT _ Freddie Mac, Clark Atlanta and other black
colleges are working to develop an education program that will help
students develop good credit habits. About 48 percent of
African-Americans have bad credit, vs. 27 percent of whites,
according to a survey by mortgage lender Freddie Mac. (Poole,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
