   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-RYDER-PRIDE _ While they appear to be a much stronger team,
the Americans are being characterized, with some justification, as
money-hungry athletes short on pride after the pay-for-play
controversey at the PGA. Several golfers, including Phil Mickelson,
David Duval, Mark O'Meara and Tiger Woods, complained about money,
causing captain Ben Crenshaw to unload his emotions about playing
for country and pride. The Europeans, on the other hand, who have
won the Cup the last two times, have come out publicly to say that
winning for one's country is all that matters. Period. (Sheeley,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
